<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[869,1493,1274,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,1003,1274,1299]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Discussion:</emphasis>
The pattern of maculae on the fore wings of the female is similar to that of the 
<typeStatus box="[1250,1353,1306,1331]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
. This species was described based on a macropterous male collected inside a cave, without incidence of light, in the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[869,920,1402,1427]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Pará</collectingRegion>
, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1039,1099,1402,1427]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues, H. D. D. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F." box="[1113,1435,1402,1427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="183 - 188" refId="ref6023" refString="Rodrigues, H. D. D. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. 2016 b. A new species, new synonymy, and notes on Paravelia Breddin (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Veliidae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 56 (17): 183 - 188." type="journal article" year="2016">Rodrigues &amp; Moreira, 2016b</bibRefCitation>
). The two females examined here also were collected inside a cave in the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[1085,1136,1466,1491]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Pará</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
